html.htmlText:
Imagine all the BEST of Prague's apartments combined into one

- 3floor apartment with rooftop, fireplace, jacuzzi, and grill
- TOP location in hearth of Prague
- PS5
- Private view to Prague castle and Old Town
- Building originally built in 1352 and listed as UNESCO heritage
- Private lift straight to the rooftop
- Newly refurbished (2017) under the supervision of London-based Wolf design studio
- 310m2
- Perfect public transport connection (TRAM, TUBE - 50m)

Welcome to the King's Apartment!

The King's apartment is located in the heart of Prague - Old Town.

Within a short walking distance you can find these historical treasures:
- 100 m Rudolfinum - renowned Opera House
- 100 m Four Seasons Hotel
- 100 m Picturesque Vltava river going through the city
- 250 m Charles Bridge registered in the UNESCO
- 300 m Old Town Square where is famous Astronomical Clock

Transportation:
- 10 m from the apartment there is tram and metro stops
- 50 m Old Town Square
- 50 m distance a wide variety of restaurants, shops, coffee shops, ATS machines,

The entire apartment is available.

On the first floor there are 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, kitchen, sitting room and fireplace.

On the second floor there is a sofa for relaxation, double bed and access to the private terrace.
On the third floor there is private terrace with a view to Prague Castle, Hot Tube, grill, sunbathing chairs, dining table, chairs.

The house was built in 1352 and it is listed on the world heritage list.
The apartment is considered as one of the top destinations in Central Europe.

html.htmlText: We are happy to offer our help through your stay and provide with all necessary information in order to make your stay smooth and enjoyable in Prague!
Superhosts are experienced, highly rated hosts who are committed to providing great stays for guests.

hostProfileDescription.htmlText:
We are a young dynamic team which brought together a common passion for travelling, Airbnb hosting, design and desire to do things right plus with FUN!

Every team has its leaders, ours are Michal and Michael.

Michal is the reason why our apartment looks so good. At first, he was focused on industrial design and later he gradually turned onto an automotive design. He had already worked for brands like BMW, McLaren and others, until joining small design team in the UK. Nowadays he still works on various projects in London while dedicating a growing portion of his time creating and operating the most amazing apartments in Prague.

On the everyday site of the company is Michael. Thanks to his everyday work we are able to work perfectly together and provide you with the most pleasant stays in Prague possible. Instead of going to college he started working right after high school. At first, he was focusing on financial advisory, he was good and successful but it just wasn't "it". And so, he moved to Prague, where he teamed up with Michal and he started focusing on short-term lets in Prague.

And the rest of the team? All of us are passionate travellers bored with superficial holiday resorts and fabricated touristic attractions. We love coming up with various ways how to improve your stay and turn it into a positive experience that you will remember.

We love experiencing new things and meeting new people, appreciating good quality of living and seeing new cities/places genuinely and with fun. Our goal is to bring the same to you.

disclaimer.title: To protect your payment, never transfer money or communicate outside of the Airbnb website or app.

section.title: Things to know
section.additionalHouseRules:
I understand that a city tax or tourist fee is to be paid in cash on arrival in the amount of 2 EUR per person and night (or equivalent in these currencies: EUR/USD/GBP/CHF) - excluding children up to 15 years of age.

Parties are allowed under these circumstances: It is allowed to have parties on the terrace until 10 PM, then only inside (peaceful sitting with wine on the terrace or in the jacuzzi after 10 PM is also OK). It is also forbidden to damage any equipment or furniture belonging to the apartment.

I will behave respectfully and responsibly on the premises, look after the apartment's equipment, and will use its resources responsibly. I will be liable for any damage to the property.

We look forward to welcoming you to Prague soon.
